[6] Europe update
Date: Sat 28 Sep 2019
Source: The Connexion [edited]
http://www.connexionfrance.com/index.php/French-news/Health/Europe-losing-health-battle-with-measles


Europe is "losing ground" in the battle against measles, the World Health Organisation claims in a report. For the 1st time in 7 years, the number of cases is increasing in Europe: 90 000 in the 1st half of this year [2019], more than in all of 2018 (84 462).

In France, where vaccination has been mandatory for all children born after 31 Dec 2018, some 2400 cases have been reported so far this year [2019], with 2 deaths.

Most cases are among young adults who have not received the 2 required doses and are mainly in Nouvelle Aquitaine, Occitanie and PACA (France).

