[10] Philippines
Date: Fri 27 Sep 2019
Source: Manila Times [abridged, edited]
https://www.manilatimes.net/2019/09/27/news/regions/cordillera-alarmed-by-surge-in-measles-cases/622298/


Health authorities disclosed that measles cases in the different parts of the Cordillera increased by 847% from January to September this year [2019] with 985 cases compared with only 104 cases during the same period last year [2018]. Officials from the different district health units were alarmed when data obtained from the Department of Health-Cordillera office of the regional epidemiology and surveillance unit indicated there were 4 measles-related deaths recorded by the health department compared with zero deaths last year [2018].

Health officials advised the disease-reporting units in the different parts of the region to make sure every detected case will have a specimen for laboratory confirmation and timely interventions by the concerned health authorities.

[Byline: Dexter A. See]

